comment: Lemma for ~ mbfi1fseq . This lemma is not as interesting as it is long - it is simply checking that ` G ` is in fact a sequence of simple functions, by verifying that its range is in ` ( 0 ... n 2 ^ n ) / ( 2 ^ n ) ` (which is to say, the numbers from ` 0 ` to ` n ` in increments of ` 1 / ( 2 ^ n ) ` ), and also that the preimage of each point ` k ` is measurable, because it is equal to ` ( -u n [,] n ) i^i ( ``' F " ( k [,) k + 1 / ( 2 ^ n ) ) ) ` for ` k < n ` and ` ( -u n [,] n ) i^i ( ``' F " ( k [,) +oo ) ) ` for ` k = n ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 16-Aug-2014.)
